Citation.sTitle: Equilibrium Solubility of Sodium 3-Nitrobenzenesulfonate in Binary NaCl + H2O, Na2SO4 + H2O, and C2H5OH + H2O Solvent Mixtures at Elevated Temperatures from (273.15 to 323.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of sodium 3-nitrobenzenesulfonate in binary NaCl + H2O, Na2SO4 + H2O, and C2H5OH + H2O solvent mixtures were measured at elevated temperatures from (273.15 to 323.15) K by a steady-state method. The results of these measurement were correlated by a modified Apelblat equation
